+    Set ``include_empty`` to ``False`` to exclude items whose grouping
+    attribute is ``None``, an empty string, or otherwise falsy.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items in users|groupby("city", include_empty=False) %}
+          <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    Pass a ``key_transform`` callable to format the group key used for
+    display, without affecting how items are grouped.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for year, items in users|groupby("birthday.year", key_transform=str) %}
+          <li>{{ year }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.2
+        Added the ``include_empty`` and ``key_transform`` parameters.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
